"That'll be 20 zorkmids," the shopkeeper said. Cody blinked, then hurriedly reached into his pouch and pulled out a handful of gold. The man beamed and stepped forward collecting the money from Cody's outstretched hand. Cody barely heard the man's thanks for his business, seeing a light at the end of the tunnel that was this restaurant and, indeed, the entire Warrens.
